This paper is about an evolutionary algorithm for global optimization, which falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization. Specifically, it focuses on the estimation of distribution algorithm (EDA), which is a type of model-based evolutionary algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as Gaussian modeling and covariance matrix estimation, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency and performance of the algorithm, which can be evaluated using statistical analysis and experimental results. This falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper also involves the use of an archive to store historical solutions, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the algorithm in various fields, such as control systems and optimization problems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
